Interface JASerializable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    App, Box, Bytes, Collection<ENTRY_TYPE>, Durable, FLenS<RESPONSE_TYPE>, IncDes, JABoolean, JADouble, JAFloat, JAInteger, JAList<ENTRY_TYPE>, JALong, JAMap<KEY_TYPE,VALUE_TYPE>, JAString, MapEntry<KEY_TYPE,VALUE_TYPE>, Root, Tuple, Union, VLenS<RESPONSE_TYPE>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AppBase, BList, BMap, BoxImpl, BytesImpl, CollectionImpl, DurableImpl, FLenScalar, IncDesImpl, IntegerBMap, IntegerSMap, JABooleanImpl, JADoubleImpl, JAFloatImpl, JAIntegerImpl, JALongImpl, JAStringImpl, LongBMap, LongSMap, MapEntryImpl, RootImpl, Scalar, SList, SMap, StringBMap, StringSMap, TupleImpl, UnionImpl, VLenScalar
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    public interface JASerializable
    All incrementally deserializable objects must implement this interface and return a reference to their durable part.
